issues.description: The `Milkable` interfaceâ€™s `messageOnMilk()` method is specified in the problem statement to return a `String` and return the message `"[Animal Type] [name] is milked"`, but in the solution repository the interface declares it as returning `boolean`, and implementations print to stdout and return `true`. This mismatches the intended signature and return type and would confuse students and break the tests.
issues.suggested_fix: Change `Milkable.messageOnMilk()` to return `String` rather than `boolean`, and update the `Seal` and `Goat` implementations to return the milked message string instead of printing and returning a boolean.
